000.0,"total_cash":57450000.0,"total_cash_per_share":11.571,"total_debt":70176000.0,"debt_to_equity":8.062,"enterprise_value":731187264.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":6.89,"enterprise_to_revenue":0.529,"earnings_growth":-0.459,"shares_outstanding":4960500.0,"float_shares":585841.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.88198996,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-1.283,"fifty_two_week_high":315.0,"fifty_two_week_low":141.15,"fifty_day_average":181.017,"two_hundred_day_avg":219.56924,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":370.0,"all_time_low":143.65,"long_business_summary":"B & A Packaging India Limited engages in the manufacture and sale of paper sacks and flexible laminates in India. The company provides paper sacks, such as baggage normal and AQC tea, and baggage high porous and high porous plus sacks. It also offers flexible laminates, including center seal pouches for snacks; 3 side seal pouches for sea food, medical purposes, tea industries, atta, chattu, and beverage industries; 2 side seal pouches for sanitary pads; sea food pouches for frozen sea food; standy pouches for tea industries, sea food, dry food, and pasta producing; 5 side seal pouches with side gusset for tea industries; and center seal pouches with side gusset for tissue papers. In addition, the company provides off center seal pouches with side gusset; dip tea pouches for tea industries; vac. pack bags for tea, food packaging, and pharmaceutical industries; flap type pouches for textile and pen industries; liner bags for commodities comprising sugar, tea, coffee, food grains, spices, salt, cereals, fertilizers, chemicals, etc.; shrink films for beverages, cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, and food and consumer goods packaging; and BOPP tapes. It also exports its products. The company was formerly known as B & A Multiwall Packaging Limited and changed its name to B & A Packaging India Limited in June 2010. The company was incorporated in 1986 and is headquartered in Kolkata, India. B & A Packaging India Limited is a subsidiary of B & A Limited."}}